<span class="displaytext"><i>in response to the proposal being floated today in florida to address the primary situation, (candidate last) campaign deputy communications director phil singer issued the following statement:</i> <p>"considering that the (candidate last) campaign is essentially disenfranchising 1.7 million floridians who are now signaling that they will vote for the (PARTY NAME) if their votes aren't counted, there is a very simple solution: honor the vote that took place in january. </p><p>"everyone was on the ballot, no candidate had an unfair advantage (even if senator (candidate last) was the only candidate to advertise) and it won't cost an extra penny. </p><p>"at this point, that seems to be the best option. senator (candidate last) should embrace it and abandon his current position which disenfranchises approximately 1.7 million people."</p></span>



